</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,655,1689]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,480,798,825]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,473,798,825]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head rounded trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[787,870,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head convex, frons slightly concave. Marginal carina broad, narrowing anterior to 
<emphasis box="[877,933,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">dsms</emphasis>
, deeply displaced and widened at osculum. Ventral anterior plate rounded, with concave anterior margin and sinuous lateral margins. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,233,906,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi wide, bulging slightly. Pre- and post-ocular nodi large, connected dorsally by broad ocular band. Marginal temporal carina slender. Gular plate triangular, lateral margins convex. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[288,419,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–44" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[240,1349,191,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[230,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 43–44. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 43, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 44, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825575/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 43–44</figureCitation>
. Base pigmentation translucent; head nodi, proepimera, and metepisterna medium brown; much of preantennal head (dotted line in 
<figureCitation box="[615,698,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
), margins of antennal sockets, gular plate, sternal plates V–VI (in some specimens also posterior end of sternal plate IV), subgenital plates, and central part of female tergopleurite IX+X pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,655,1689]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1122,1149]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[741,824,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–44" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[240,1349,191,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[230,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 43–44. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 43, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 44, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825575/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
; tergopleurites IV–V with 1 
<emphasis box="[1146,1168,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">ss</emphasis>
on each side and tergopleurite VI with 2 
<emphasis box="[363,385,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">ss</emphasis>
on each side; sternite IV with 1 
<emphasis box="[759,789,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">sts</emphasis>
one each side; male abdominal segment VI with 1 
<emphasis box="[1375,1400,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme rounded, narrowing slightly distally, lateral margins slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1314,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome with antero-lateral extensions (
<figureCitation box="[630,715,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), anterior margin concave. Mesosomal lobes divergent distally. Distal margin of mesosome roughly flat. Gonopore with bluntly triangular antero-lateral extensions. Dorsal fringe tilted posteriorly. Chaetotaxy: 1 ventral 
<emphasis box="[607,679,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">gpmes</emphasis>
microseta on each side of distal gonopore; 2 
<emphasis box="[1204,1269,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">lpmes</emphasis>
microsetae on each side on mesosomal lobes, with distal 
<emphasis box="[622,687,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">lpmes</emphasis>
near distal margin; 1 dorsal 
<emphasis box="[1003,1061,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">ames</emphasis>
microseta on each side median to dorsal fringes. Parameres and 
<emphasis box="[489,564,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[630,713,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[952,1036,1375,1401]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,655,1689]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1410,1437]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[770,853,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–44" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[240,1349,191,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[230,1356,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 43–44. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 43, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 44, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825575/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
. Subgenital plate hexagonal (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1268,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–49" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1399,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[169,1419,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 45–49. Indoceoplanetes (Indoceoplanetes) zambica new species ex Coracina pectoralis. 45, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 46, male genitalia, dorsal view. 47, male mesosome, ventral view. 48, male paramere, dorsal view. 49, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825577/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
), distal margin flat. Vulval margin concave medianly, with 2–3 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[857,901,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vms</emphasis>
and 0–1 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[1196,1230,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 5–7 slender 
<emphasis box="[239,276,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 1–3 
<emphasis box="[764,801,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vos</emphasis>
distal to 
<emphasis box="[904,938,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vss</emphasis>
and substantially longer than 
<emphasis box="[1273,1317,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[284,367,1519,1545]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
